SYMPTOM_TEXT: presented to the clinic to receive her first dose of Pediatric Pfizer (Lot FK5127-H). She received a dose at 0944 to her RD and moved to the observation area with her mother. At approximately 0950, she c/o nausea to the observation RN and had a small amount of emesis. RN alerted another RN to assist. At 0955, the client transferred to the cot and accepted water, drinking it without difficulty or further emesis. She reported that she felt better after laying down. SPO2 at 0955 was 95% on RA, HR was 84. She denied any sensation of itchiness, tingling, or difficulty breathing and showed no signs of facial/tongue/lip swelling or rashes. She reported that she had been very anxious about receiving the vaccine before injection and that she has a fear of needles.  At 1000, she sat up on the cot, denied nausea and reported that she felt ?90% normal.? SPO2 was 98% on RA, HR was 94. At 1004, she rose and transferred to a nearby chair without difficulty. Visual assessment of facial tissues continued to show no signs of swelling, no rashes noted on skin. The client and her mother were educated on s/s anaphylactic responses, what to watch for, and when to seek medical care. Aside from the brief episode of N/V, she exhibited no s/s of an allergic reaction. She remained under observation until 1019, at which point she reported she felt ?better than ever? and her SPO2 was 99% on RA with an HR of 83. She exited the facility at 1020 with her mother, to be monitored by her mother at home.

THERE WAS MISS COMMUNICATION BETWEEN PHARMACIST, PARENT, AND PT. THE MOTHER CALLED IN (OTHER SON) AND PT CAME IN THE ROOM. I ASKED THE PT IF HE WAS (other son) AND HE CONFIRMED HE WAS. THE PFIZER ADULT DOSE OF 0.3ML WAS ADMINISTERED. ONCE PT WAS CALLED THE MOTHER SAID PT WAS THE 1ST CHILD THAT CAME IN WHICH IS WHERE WE BOTH CAUGHT THE ERROR. SHE TOLD ME THIS HAPPENS EVEN AT HOME REGULARLY ONE WILL COME IN THINKING THE OTHER CHILD WAS CALLED. I EXPLAINED I EVEN ASKED THE CHILD IF HE WAS (other son) AND HE SAID YES. SHE SAID IT WAS OKAY. I COUNSELED THE PTS MOTHER AND THE PT OF THE POSSIBLE SIDE EFFECTS. SHE DID MENTION AFTER THE FACT THAT HE HAD A RUNNY NOSE BUT WAS NOT RUNNING FEVER OR ANY OTHER PROBLEMS. I ALSO CAUTIONED THE MOTHER THAT IF THE CHILD STARTED FEELING PAIN IN HIS CHEST TO TAKE HIM IMMEDIATELY TO THE ER OR AN URGENT CARE AS IT MAY BE A FORM OF PERICARDITIS (INFLAMMATION OF THE HEARTS LINING) WHICH THEY SHOULD BE ABLE TO ADDRESS. I TOLD HER I WOULD DOCUMENT THIS INCIDENT IN HIS PROFILE AND IF SHE NEEDED ANYTHING FOR PT TO PLEASE DONT HESISTATE AND CALL. I RECOMMENDED CHILDRENS TYLENOL OR IBUPROFEN OTC IF SHE NEEDED FOR THE CHILDREN AND TO FOLLOW DIRECTIONS ON BACK OF THE PACKAGING. WILL FOLLOW UP IN 2 DAYS FROM TODAY-  12-2-21

Client received 2nd dose in primary pediatric Pfizer vaccine series. Client was seated in chair when receiving vaccination. Approximately 2 minutes after administration, client lost consciousness, bumped head on back of chair and was lowered to the floor by parent and vaccinator. Client lost consciousness for approximately 15 seconds, but became fully responsive immediately after and was able to recall events prior to loss of consciousness. Vital signs were within appropriate ranges. An ice pack was provided for the client's head, client had no complaints of concussion symptoms. Client was given a juice box and pretzels. Client remained in the exit area for 30 minutes to monitor for further adverse events. Client improved with food and drink and was released into the care of parent with recommendation to follow up with pediatrician if new symptoms present or worsen.

The nurse and myself assessed the patient who was diaphoretic, lethargic. At time of assessment it 1731  was noted  that patient was tachycardic, had thready radial pulse and the nurse observed her eyes roll back in her head and would not respond to verbal stimuli. 911 was called. Patient regained full consciousness  and was moved out of the Cafeteria area to a calmer location. Mother stated that child had not eaten recently and was given a bottle of orange juice. After consuming the orange juice, child seemed to ""perk back up"" and stated that she felt a little better.  Ambulance squad arrived and transported child

As the symptoms progressed, the nurse called 911 at approximately 11:00 am.  Symptoms began to clear in transit to the ER.  By approximately 12:30 pm symptoms were mostly gone except for headache.  Her headache subsided over the next 24 hours.  The ER doctors, patient, diagnosed patient with a hemiplegic migraine.  patient had never experienced any of these symptoms previously. patient is scheduled to follow up with a neurologist on 12/15/2021.

Trying antihistamine/hydrocortisone  to see if it?s more of an allergic reaction to the vaccine.  First shot he did have a small rash, but nothing like these severe shooting, inconsistent pain associated with the second. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient developed four lesions consistent with pityriasis rosea within two days of receiving the first dose (11/6/21) of the Pfizer vaccine on her chest, abdomen, and groin. Patient received the second dose of the Pfizer vaccine (11/29/21) and developed a fifth lesion on her back within hours of receiving that second dose. Her physician referred her to a dermatologist. The patient has never experienced any sort of skin reactions prior vaccines, all have been tolerated well. The lesions do not appear to change since initial development, but the number has increased by one within 24 hours of the second dose.

All_symptoms: Abdominal pain lower Asthenia Balance disorder Dizziness Dysarthria
SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1715: Patient noted ""dizziness"" about 15 minutes post-injection. Denied respiratory distress. No abnormal skin presentations noted, oral mucosa moist, pink, no swelling noted. Patient B/P 95/77, HR 76, O2 sat 99%  on room air, lung sounds clear throughout. Bilateral grips weak, appeared to be trembling.   1718: Patient recline with legs elevated, took deep breaths and coughed. c/o worsening dizziness. Denied nausea. Temp 98.7  1730: Pt noted her throat felt tight and it was ""hard to swallow."" Pt stated it was ""getting harder to take a breath.""   No respiratory distress noted, lung sounds clear throughout, O2 sat 99% on RA. Nurse notified on-call physician, prepared to activate emergency response. Mother declined emergency intervention, patient stated she could ""breathe fine"" and stated her throat was not as tight as previously reported.  1745: Pt attempted to stand, legs began to shake and patient appeared unable to bear weight or walk. Nurse and mother assisted patient to sit.  Patient exhibited  slurred, slow speech. Pt eyes closed and head fell forward. When pt roused, she c/o headache, fatigue, and moderate to severe LLQ pain that was tender to palpation. Pt guarding (L) ABD. Temp 99.5. B/P 125/80, HR 80,  O2 sat 98% on RA, lung sounds remained clear throughout.   Nurse initiated emergency response.   1800: When EMT's arrived, pt was able yto ambulate with assistance, appeared weak, unsteady but able to bearweight. Pt A+O x 4. Mother accompanied patient to ambulance.  NOTE: Patient mother noted unusual tiredness and lethargy ""over the last 2 days. It has been hard to wake her (patient) up.""  Patient c/o intermittent stomach pain, LLQ, over past two days. Current nausea and headache.

I took my 10 year old daughter to the Pharmacy in store.   The second dose of Covid vaccine leaked out of the arm while the person was administering it on my daughters arm.  I saw mostly all the liquid from the shot run down her deltoid right up to her elbow. My daughter felt the initial poke of the needle but I am a 100% sure she DID NOT receive the full dosage. The person then tried to tell me it was the  ?alcohol from the alcohol wipe?.   I wrote to my daughters doctor about this and explained the situation to her after she called me to discuss it, she agreed that based on my description of the incident, that the dose was likely misadministered and to get her another dose.  When I took my daughter back to the Pharmacy today, they said they did not have the vaccine in stock and tried sending me to another Pharmacy. They called the other Pharmacy which said they were not comfortable giving my doctor the vaccine even though they had it in stock. Now I?m not sure how and where she can get her second dose.

All_symptoms: Papule Rash Rash erythematous Rash pruritic
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Twelve days after receiving the vaccine, a patchy rash erupted all over his body. It was itchy and was on his face, neck, trunk, buttocks, thighs, lower legs, upper arms and hands, with large red patches and new papules that continued to appear over the subsequent ten days. Since he was scheduled for his second shot on the 24th, we delayed the second vaccine to give time for the rash to run its course so that we didn't confound any symptoms observed with the second vaccine. Rash subsided (no new rashes) around the 25th. Second vaccine scheduled for November 30th.
LAB_DATA: No tests. We took him to the doctor who said it wasn't possible to say what caused the rash and that the papules looked like insect bites. He recommended antihistamines. But it's November, there are no insects in the house, and our son has been isolated (not even attending school) since March 2020. We tried oral kids' Zyrtec and Benadryl, and topical calamine lotion, but no relief.

All_symptoms: Diarrhoea Generalised tonic-clonic seizure Nightmare Pain in extremity Seizure
SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient had the Pfizer 5-11 shot on November 20 at 12:45 pm.  He seemed to have mild side effects initially (sore arm and diarrhea).  The next morning he fell asleep during church sermon and after it was done (~9:30 am), we woke him and he started having a tonic clonic seizure lasting about 1 minute.  He was checked by pediatrician and MRI/EEG scheduled for December 22, 2021.  Today, November 28, he came down around 6 am complaining about having a nightmare and so he crawled into bed with me.  He fell asleep and then had another seizure around 6:30 am lasting about 30 seconds. Patient had no history of seizures or any other health issues prior to Pfizer 5-11 being administered,
LAB_DATA: No tests done yet, but we have an MRI and EEG scheduled for December 22, 2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The night of the vaccination, the patient experienced a fever of 104 degree and greater according to the mother. The fever responded to oral fever reducer immediately. The patient also experienced hallucinations the night of the vaccination and for 2 more consecutive nights. The hallucinations would begin in the evening and continue into the night. The mother called their pediatrician and the adverse effects were noted in the patient chart. The pediatrician recommended the patient continue with the vaccine series and complete the second dose but for the mother to treat with fever reducer on a scheduled basis for 24 hours after vaccination.

In the process of receiving liquid steroids and liquid antibiotics to try to stop the spreading. No issues with breathing and will follow up with pediatrician this week.

All_symptoms: Electrocardiogram normal Feeling abnormal Syncope Unresponsive to stimuli
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 26 hours after receiving the 2nd dose of the pediatric Pfizer/BioNTech COVID19 vaccine, female child was getting dressed and as I (her mother) was brushing her hair, she turned around and told me, ""I don't feel good"" and then fainted. At first I wasn't sure what happened, so I got her onto the floor and then called 911 and by the time they answered (likely approximately 30-45 seconds from the onset of symptoms) she was responsive again. The ambulance arrived within minutes and she was evaluated by the EMTs. The EMTs then called the ER doctor that said she should be brought to the emergency room to be seen by the doctor.
LAB_DATA: She had blood pressure/pulse ox monitoring both in the ambulance and in the hospital. They did an EKG in the hospital, all on 11/27/2021. All tests came back normal and she was discharged from the ER without being admitted. So far, she has not had any additional problems.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Saturday, November 27, 2021 client came for vaccination POD accompanied by his Mother for his second Covid-19 Pfizer pediatric dose. During assessment questions, Mom stated to RN, patient received his first dose Covid-19 Pfizer pediatric dose (LOT #: FK5127) on 11/6/21 in his right arm and and a flu shot on his left arm. Two weeks later, Mom stated patient experienced a ""pinching sensation"" on left side of chest. Mom stated patient would experience this sensation once or two times a day intermittently. The last time it happened was on 11/25/21, Thanksgiving day. Mom stated they spoke with his MD who recommended a 30 minute wait after second vaccination. Patient has no chronic medical conditions and takes Loratadine every day due to allergies to cats and dust. Lead Nurse elevated to Vaccine Operations Lead who was on site, who consulted with County MD. Per County MD, Pfizer pediatric dose was approved and advised client to receive his second dose of Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine with 30 minute observation. Client was vaccinated with Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine (LOT #: FK5618) in his left arm at 2:07 PM. Client and client's Mother was educated by RN on signs and symptoms of adverse reactions and when to go to the ED/call MD. Client's Mother was also encouraged to sign-up on v-safe. Client experienced no adverse reaction while waiting in Observation Area and left vaccination site with a steady gait at 2:45 pm.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pfizer vacc covid-19 5-11y 1st dose @ 12:30pm, no reaction immediately post vaccination. I asked the patient's mother and the patient to come back into the immunization room. After noting the redness in the patient's ears, I asked and the mother agreed to give the patient a dose of diphenhydramine to control the allergic reaction. Per the mother, the patient is 65lbs therefore per emergency protocol the patient was given 12ml of diphenhydramine12.5mg/5ml x1dose (30mg) with water. We observed patient for 30min. and since the mother expressly acknowledges that all symptoms of the adverse reaction have passed, the patient was released w/the mother. We gave instruction for the mother to contact md if patient's/ re-appeared. Per the patient's mother, the patient's PCP is (Privacy), I was unable to reach since the office is closed on the weekend. I will contact the patient's mother in 24hrs to follow-up.

LAB_DATA: We went to the ER on 11/26/2021. They took chest xrays and I think xrays of the throat. Test results were negative. He only had a sporadic barking cough by then.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Mom reports he was otherwise in his normal state of health on 11/11 when he got his first COVID-19 vaccine in his left deltoid. He had some pain there the first day and then this resolved--he did well for a week. On the night of 11/18 he began complaining of a little pain in the left upper arm again and went to sleep. On 11/19 AM, he noticed and showed mom that he had difficulty extending his wrist and fingers on that hand. He also has some pain in his lateral arm just above the elbow and some itching of the dorsal surface of the hand, both which started in the previous 24 hours. He was evaluated for acute left wrist drop at Hospital ED, exam notable for ""left wrist drop, very weak left finger extensors and weak thumb abduction."" He underwent work up there including lab work and MRI (below). He was ultimately discharged with suspected peripheral radial nerve neuropathy of the left hand.

All_symptoms: Acute respiratory distress syndrome Chest X-ray normal Cough Respiratory syncytial virus infection Stridor
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Acute respiratory distress consistent with RSV. Went to Urgent Treatment Center as condition was worsening. Patient showed stridor.  No RSV test was given, and the doctor assumed RSV because he had received his COVID vaccine and had a history of croup. 16mL intramuscular dexamethasone injection was given, symptoms subsided within an hour and disappeared by the start of the next day.  He received the second Pfizer dose on the 23rd, and eight hours later showed the same coughing and stridor approximately eight hours later, with acute symptoms. We went to the same Urgent Treatment Center where he received albuterol sulfate via nebulizer, and oral dexamethasone of the same dosage. The Urgent Treatment Center referred us to the Emergency Room. We traveled to Hospital where he received two breathing treatments of racemic epinephrine. His symptoms did not subside, but because O2 and heart rate were stable for the duration of the time that we were there - even when he slept - they sent us home. He awoke with the stridor gone and with no further symptoms.

All_symptoms: Condition aggravated Fall Hyperhidrosis Lethargy Loss of consciousness
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Per report by RN who vaccinated patient:  Pt received 1st Covid vaccine, and after the vaccination was standing by her mother watching her sister get vaccinated.  Suddenly she fainted, slumped to floor; she did not hit her head. She lost consciousness for less than 10 seconds. Her father picked her up and put her on his lap.  1st Aid RN and EMT on site responded. Applied ice pack to back of her neck. Pt was pale, diaphoretic and oriented x3. At this time, the father revealed that child has history of fainting with shots (which parents did not inform clinical staff of prior to vaccination). Dad carried child to 1st aid station where she was assessed and monitored. She was placed supine on cot with feet elevated; pallid and slow to verbal response. 10:35 vital signs B/P 102/68, pulse 81 bpm, O2 99%.  Pt slowly regained color, had water and crackers. Vital signs sitting up B/P 98/68, O2 98%. Pt still slow to respond and lethargic. Paramedics called at 11:00, arrived at 11:10. Assessed child and interviewed parents, made decision to not transport. Pt became more animated, color returned and able to stand and walk safely on her own. 11:20 Family left clinic.

In the meantime, her mother came over and sat next to her and asked if she had a seizure.  I said that I did not believe she had a seizure.  Mother also said she had no history of seizures or fainting.  Just about then the young lady popped up totally alert and able to answer questions from her mother.  Her mother said she felt like she had a fever and wanted to sit there for a while.  She asked if I could take her blood pressure and I told her I did not believe we had a monitor.  They left after about 10 minutes.

All_symptoms: Extra dose administered Injection site extravasation Pyrexia
SYMPTOM_TEXT: A small amount of vaccine leaked out from the arm of a 6 yo during administration of dose. I could not find guidance in the FDA EUA document, but the CDC interim clinical considerations guidance does address (last updated 11/19/21) and now seems to recommend more clearly to repeat the dose immediately for lower than authorized dose administered e.g. leaked out:  Lower-than-authorized dose volume administered of the correct formulation (e.g., leaked out, equipment failure, recipient pulled away): Repeat dose immediately (no minimum interval). See: https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/covid-19/clinical-considerations/covid-19-vaccines-us.html. Based on this, spoke to family, reviewed the limited data available from the phase 1 portion of the Pfizer trial, both 10 and 20 mcg doses were overall well tolerated, though high fever did develop in one child after dose 2 of the 20 mcg dose, lasting 3 days. Since this patient has both an underlying urea cycle defect and periodic fever syndrome, risk of fever bears consideration due to a higher predisposition as well as potential risk of metabolic sequelae arising from fever- so the discussion mostly focused around this increased risk of fever/ reactogenicity. Parents had a chance to talk to his geneticist and discuss amongst themselves, weighed risks vs benefits, felt they could likely manage a fever if it developed by working closely with his genetics team and they ultimately desired to ensure optimal protection by vaccination. He returned to the clinic, and was re-dosed without event. We have not had any other reports of this. The nurse is a seasoned vaccinator so I would trust her vaccination method. It could be an issue with the syringe itself or a faulty syringe that was leaking around the hub.

Client received the 1st dose Pfizer COVID vaccine (lot# FK5618) in the L arm at 0935. After vaccination the client and his mother were seated in observation for 15 minutes. At approximately 0951 the client began to slump over in his chair and his mother slowly lowered him to the ground and asked for help. RN immediately responded to assess the client. RN removed clients mask, assisted in laying client in the supine position, and assessed a patent airway while RN took client's vitals. By the time client was assessed he was responsive to stimuli and his mother reported he was not responsive to stimuli for approximately 2 seconds. At approximately 0953 client was A&O x4 with no SOB and speaking in full sentences. Client vitals were BP 100/44 BP in the R arm laying down, HR 88, and RR 14. RN assessed client for injuries and observed no injury to the head or rest of body. Client appeared moderately diaphoretic. Client reported no pain, headache, numbness, tingling, or trouble breathing. At 1000 RN assisted client to the zero gravity chair. Client reported no dizziness when standing. Client was placed laying down in zero gravity chair. RN provided client with a water bottle, juice box, and graham crackers. RN observed client take sips of juice and finish his water bottle. Client ate graham crackers. Client reported he ate a waffle for breakfast and his mother stated that he has not had any water to drink.  At 1005 client's O2 saturation level was 96% and HR was 54. RN assessed strong equal grip, strong and equal pulses, cap refill <3 seconds, and skin warm and pink to touch. At 1006 RN advised client to remain in observation for 30 minutes and reviewed ER precuations with client's mother and advised to f/u with client's PCP. At 1007 client denied SOB, dizziness, nausea, headache, numbness, and tingling. Client reported ""i feel Better now"". At 1040 client left the vaccine with his mother and RN observed a steady and symmetrical gait.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient developed R inguinal adenopathy (1cm x 2) on 11/13/21.  On 11/14/21 she developed an erythematous papular rash on the R lower extremity and a few similar lesions on her chest and back.  Was seen by urgent care and told rash were bites.  Was seen at on  11/15 CBC, BMP, CRP drawn, all WNL.  The lesions on her legs became purpuric on 11/19/21.  Seen again at on 11/22, inguinal adenopathy decreasing in size, labs repeated including UA which showed microscopic hematuria.  At no time did she have fever.  No abdominal pain, no joint pain, no headache, no itching. BP 93/62--normal   Given lower extremity rash and microscopic hematuria, we are calling this HSP but it is a very soft diagnosis.  The feeling is that this is vaccine related, whether it be HSP or just a purpuric rash.

On Sunday around 8pm patient got extremely tired before bed. This was unusual for him. He was falling asleep on the couch. He complained of a headache which he maybe only ever had once in his life. He wasn't running a fever. He woke up at 5:30am throwing up. It was almost all yellow bile. He slept on the couch the entire day waking up briefly and threw up probably 7 or 8 times throughout the day. He couldn't even watch TV he felt so exhausted and sick. He never ran a fever the whole time. He was able to urinate and take a couple ounces of fluid around 6pm Sunday. So Sunday at 5pm was the last time he threw up. He threw up when we tried to give him Motrin.  We did have a call with a Dr and we're told to go to emergency room if he gets better or can't keep fluids down.  The next day (today that I'm writing this) he still spent most of the on the couch but was drinking and able to keep small food down. We have 2 adults and 2 other kids in the house and no one has been sick but him.
LAB_DATA: Temperature checks. Never had a fever.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 30 minutes after receiving the COVID-19 vaccine, my daughter started experiencing trouble getting a good breath. I took her back to the hospital where she received the COVID-19 vaccine and they immediately walked us to the ER. Her blood pressure and oxygen levels checked immediately before taken back to a room. A doctor came in and suggested trying some Benadryl and just watching/monitoring her. About 30 minutes after receiving Benadryl, her headache subsided. Within an hour, her breathing was much easier. She was monitored for a total of 4 hours. During that time, her blood pressure was checked periodically and oxygen levels monitored.

All_symptoms: Eye movement disorder Fall Loss of consciousness Syncope
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Upon completion of administering the vaccination, when the guest was getting up she fainted as she was going to observation. Guest fell to floor, I was 5' away at another vaccination station.  Staff who vaccinated her responded directly to her. She was unconscious and eyes rolled back. She was out for about 10 seconds. Vitals were taken and guest was talking to us. I left guest with staff and two other RN's and called emergency for an ambulance from EMS. We monitored guest until EMS arrival.  EMS was given report and care was transferred to EMS. They put her on the stretcher and transported. to  Hospital. Talked with her mother Monday 11/22/2021 and she said she was checked in ER and it was determined that it was a Syncopel  Episode and she was released.
LAB_DATA: Unknown, pt was checked in ER.

All_symptoms: Alanine aminotransferase increased Antibody test Aspartate aminotransferase increased Bacterial test Blood alkaline phosphatase increased
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient became febrile on 11/17/21 and developed bright erythematous rash that was worse at creases. She was treated with PO amoxicillin due to presumed scarlet fever. She continued to be febrile and rash became maculopapular throughout body. She was seen in ED on 11/21 and had labs that showed slightly elevated liver enzymes and UA showed pyuria without any UTI symptoms. She was tested for mononucleosis and negative. She was given Rocephin IM in ED and switched to cephalexin as physician concerned rash was from mononucleosis. She then continued to fever and developed conjunctivitis. Patient was admitted to Pediatric Floor on 11/23 to rule out MIS-C but on day of admission CBC and inflammatory markers were nearly normal with downtrending LFTs. She was started on doxycycline to treat murine typhus as it is endemic in the region and Rocephin empirically while awaiting cultures. She has been afebrile since admission on 11/23 and had a normal ECHO by cardiology.

AFTER RECEIVING PFIZER PEDIATRIC VACCINE - PT FELT DIZY AND LIGHT HEADED. TOOK PT'S BP - BP WAS LOW 80/60. GAVE PT SNACK AND WATER AND RETOOK BP 3 MINUTES LATER. BP WAS RISING TO 90/80. WAITED ANOTHER 5 MINUTES AND TOOK THE BP AGAIN - BP WAS 108/75. TOLD PARENT THAT THIS WAS A GOOD BLOOD PRESSURE. THE CHILD STATED THEY WERE NOT DIZZY OR LIGHT HEADED ANYMORE - HAD PT WAIT A HALF  HOUR BEFORE LETTING THEM GO BP WAS NORMAL - TOLD PARENT THAT IT WAS UP  TO THE IF THEY WANTED TO TAKE THERE CHILD TO THE ER OR  URGENT TREATMENT CENTER. THEY STATED THEY WOULD GO HOME AND IF HE STARTED TO GET DIZZY AGAIN THEY WOULD TAKE HIM TO EMERGENCY ROOM. TOLD PARENTS TO GIVE CHILD LOTS OF FLUIDS AND FOOD. CALLED PARENTS 3 HOURS LATER. THEY SAID THE CHILD WAS DOING WELL. TOLD PARENTS TO GIVE US A CALL IF ANYTHING CHANGED.

My son experienced minor discomfort on the first day and I gave him Tylenol on the night following the vaccine.  It was not until the following night 11/19/21 that he developed a fever.  He had fever higher than 102 and sweating and chills for the following 24 hours.  He also complained of nausea and later headache.  With Tylenol his temperature was still close to 100 and did not normalize until the evening of 11/20.  He felt better, but easily fatigued on Sunday.

Patient in his usual state of health received COVID-19 vaccine, dose #1, and approximately 5 hours later, started having LEFT upper and lower eyelid edema. He has never had anything similar.  No pain, no blurry vision or double vision, no redness or warmth of the site.  Seen in the ED and discharged with suggestion to give benadryl and use cold compresses to help with the swelling.  Dad states they gave 2 doses of benadryl and used the cold compresses. The swelling was resolved by the following morning.  No other symptoms.  No fully resolved on clinic follow-up today 11/22/2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Mild inflammation at injection site. Beginning stages of a rash and mild urticaria approximately 1 inch in radius centered on vaccination site. Given 12.5 mg chewable Benadryl PO. All_symptoms: Autism spectrum disorder Dehydration Urine analysis Urine ketone body present Vomiting
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Briefly, patient presents with vomiting that 10 episodes of nonbloody nonbilious per day since receiving his first Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine 48 hours ago. No fevers, diarrhea, apparent headache.     Exam (after Zofran) showed: Gen: Nontoxic appearing, no acute distress, alert and active, playing with phone; HEENT: mucus membranes dry, PERRL, EOMI, normal conjunctiva, neck supple without LAN; Card: RRR, no murmur, good perfusion; Lungs: CTAB, good air entry, no increased WOB; Abd: soft, non-tender, non-distended, no masses; Ext: warm and well perfused, moving all extremities; Skin: no rashes; GU: Testes do not appear to swollen, tender to palpation, and have normal cremasteric reflex bilaterally     Symptoms likely due to post vaccine reaction versus viral illness with component of gastroenteritis. Less likely appendicitis or other concerning intraabdominal pathology given benign abdominal exam. Do not suspect increased ICP given normal neuro exam and lack of apparent HA.  GU exam is reassuring against hernia or torsion as etiology.  Given age, UTI is less likely but discussed with family and obtained urinalysis which was reassuring against UTI, ketones likely due to dehydration.  Covid swab and rapid strep sent, strep negative, COVID pending.  Given Zofran and PO challenged tolerated multiple glasses of water without vomiting. Patient safe for discharge to home with supportive care and PCP follow up, prescribed short course of zofran in case of ongoing vomiting. Family in agreement with plan and verbalize understanding of signs and symptoms to return to care. Final Diagnosis  1. Vomiting R11.10 2. Dehydration E86.0 3. Autism spectrum disorder F84.9
LAB_DATA: UA negative except for large ketones (160) Throat culture, Group A strep - negative SARS CoV-s PCR, Resp, Qual - negative

All_symptoms: Cyanosis Dysphagia Dyspnoea Pallor Throat tightness
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient complained of not being able to swallow, shortness of breath, and feeling like throat was closing.  He became extremely pale and his lips turned blue.  He was given Epinephrine Injection .3 mg.  His symptoms improved.  He was able to walk and talk after injection and never lost consciousness.  He was transferred by ambulance to ER for further evaluation and monitoring. His twin brother suffered the same symptoms about 5 minutes later- as he had received the shot about 5 min after his brother.

Heart/chest pain started on November 11 in the evening. Resolved after 10 minutes. Pediatrician said to monitor and call if it occurs again. Chest pain started a second time on November 14. Pediatrician advised to go to the ER. ER did an EKG which came back normal. ER doc ruled out serious outcomes like aneurysm, heart attack and anything related to Kawasaki disease (which he had in 2017). He continued to have chest pain into the next day (November 15). It resolved at 2:30pm, but returned around 6:30pm and resolved by the next morning. Follow up with pediatrician the next day. They believed chest pain was not related to the vaccine because it was outside of the 24 hour window and felt it was more likely costochondritis. He had one more incident of chest pain on November 16 around 2:30pm and resolved by 3pm. Asked cardiology to schedule an echocardiogram, but have not heard from them yet and don't see much of a reason if chest pain has resolved.

All_symptoms: Blood gases abnormal Blood pH decreased Carbon dioxide increased Death Intensive care
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Due to patient's complex PMH, provider asked that patient be monitored overnight after administration of COVID vaccine.  Patient was moved from PICU to general peds floor due to improvement in condition on Thursday.  Vaccine was administered that evening.  Patient did well.  Remained on room air.  Was discharged home on Saturday.  On Monday morning, father checked on patient and she was found pulseless and not breathing.  It is unclear whether or not patient was placed on home CPAP during the night.  EMS called.  Patient arrived to ED as a CPR in progress.  Patient presented with a pH of <6.  Last known well 9pm the evening prior.  Patient expired at  11/22/21 at 11:05 CST.
LAB_DATA: Blood gas was done indicating pH<6, high CO2.
HISTORY: PMH of twin to twin transfusion born at erm, neuroimaging showed significant loss of gray-white matter, hydrocephalus s/p VP shunt, spastic CP, seizure disorder.  Use CPAP at home at night.

The patient forehead turned purple which was clearly visible to staff and pharmacist. Patient requested to  use the rest room and could not hold on any longer. Mother said she cannot come to the restroom as her second child had received the vaccine and is waiting for 15 minutes to pass so that they can go home. The patient used the restroom and said she is felling better. The mother said her daughter has previously suffered panic attacks. The patient color was back to normal and informed the pharmacist that she feels ok now. The pharmacist called the mother at home at 4:45 pm to check on the patient. Mother informed the Rph that she is doing well and thanked for the follow up call. The mother was requested to make online appointment three weeks later for the second shot.
HISTORY: patient had previous incidences of panic attack.

All_symptoms: Extra dose administered No adverse event
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was scheduled to receive a flu shot but instead received another dose of the pediatric Pfizer Covid 19 vaccine in error.  First dose was on 11/10/21. No side effects reported.

All_symptoms: Abdominal discomfort Cold sweat Malaise Muscle rigidity Pallor
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient fainted while on her way to the observation area after vaccination.  She quickly regained conscious, but was pale and in cold sweats.  Her extremities were very rigid.   We lay her on the floor.   EMT arrived within 10 minutes.    She was much relaxed, but still complained not feeling well, especially her stomach.   Patient was taken hospital for further checkup. I spoke to pt in the evening.  Pt is already home.  She is feeling fine.

PATIENT FAINTED AFTER RECEIVED THE PEDIATRIC PFIZER VACCINE.  PATIENT WAS PALE.  WE LET PATIENT REST ON FLOOR FOR FEW MINUTES. THEN PATIENT WAS LIFTED UPRIGHT AND SAT IN THE CHAIR FOR A FEW MORE MINUTES. THEN PATIENT SAT IN THE WAITING AREA AND PATIENT WAS MONITORED FOR 30 MINUTES.  PATIENT WAS FINE AFTERWORDS AND PALE FACE RETURNED NORMAL AND THE PATIENT WHEN HOME WITH FAMILY. NO OTHER TREATMENT WAS NEEDED.

Within minutes after vaccination, client reported dizziness. Client only ate breakfast and had not eaten for several hours. The client reported dizziness that slowly resolved itself. Client provided with snack and juice. The clients symptoms were completely resolved within 30 minutes.

Patient was a 10 year old Male that administered one dose of Pfizer Pediatric (0.2mL) at 1645 on 11/19/2021 at Vaccination Clinic. After roughly a few minutes, he began to exhibit signs that were seen to be a possible allergic reaction. He began to state that he was experiencing shortness of breath. Nurses assessed the patient and began initiating emergency care on the patient. At about 1654, 911 was called and Fire Department Paramedics arrived on scene at 1703. After careful assessment by both nurses and Paramedics, the patients was ruled out as not experiencing an allergic reaction. The patient was  thought to have been suffering from anxiety, with no severe complications. No medication was administered and patient was directed to stay in Observation Area longer for safety. Patient's condition began to improve and he went home with his father.
Vomiting.

Patient told the nurse after he received his vaccine it was his second one. School nurse notified, contacted the mother and mom confirmed patient had the first covid 19 vaccine on 11.13.21.  Patient is feeling fine

All_symptoms: Electric shock sensation Erythema Oropharyngeal pain Pain in extremity Pruritus
SYMPTOM_TEXT: patient received 1st dose of Pfizer (5-11) Covid-19 vaccine on Friday 11/12.  Mother called 1 week later to report the patient was suffering from side effects of the vaccine.  Symptoms started on Wed 11/17.  Her face was swollen, a little of redness but not hot; her eyes was smaller due to the puffiness/swollen face; rash on face, legs, and body; itchy skin; pain on both palms and soles of feet, this pain was on and off and was described as a shocking pain; throat pain.  Parents gave her 1 dose of Benadryl Wednesday night.  Father denied any medications at time of vaccination.  Father denied any adverse events following previous vaccines.  I advised father to seek advice from patient's doctor.

My son pointed to his center chest and said that it was hurting. No other symptoms. He received the vaccine approx 2.5 hours prior.  He said the pain lasted until he fell asleep which was about 30 minutes after the report. The pain didn?t appear to be severe - more of a noticeable annoyance to him.  He woke up the next morning (today) and said he felt fine and has been normal so far today.
The pt was given a 12 and up dose of pfizer covid-19 vaccine and she is under age 12, she is nine.

All_symptoms: Abdominal pain Diarrhoea Pyrexia SARS-CoV-2 test
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Diarrhea, fever of 100 and abdominal pain started 48 hours after getting vaccine.

All_symptoms: Bradycardia Dizziness Hyperhidrosis Loss of consciousness Pallor
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was nervous to get vaccine. She tolerated well. She moved locations to a chair and began feeling like she was going to pass out. She was bradycardic, diaphoretic and pale. She did pass out and came to a couple of seconds later. She did not fall. She was placed in a recovery position. Ice pack place on her neck. 11:45 Pulse 44,  O2 Sat 99%, Resp 12 . She was on floor for 2nd assessment in recovery position. Color was better. She was talking. Pulse 60, O2 Sat 98%, BP 88/52, Resp 12. Reassessed at 11:56 Pulse 68, O2Sat 100%, BP 95/58, Resp 12. Asked how she feels on a scale of 0-10. 0 is horrible and 10 is feels great. She states she is an 8. Had a sucker and some water. Sat up on Floor. Later sat in a chair. was feeling good. Instructed to seek medical attention if she worsens.
Patient developed a reticular non-palpable, non-purpuric rash on the CONTRALATERAL arm from which she received the vaccine, about 48 hours after immunization.  Largely resolved by the next morning.

Patient became very tense with rigid muscle upon needle insertion.  After some vaccine was instilled there was too much resistance to instill further.  Very small (difficult to measure <0.1mL) in syringe after needle removed therefore less than full volume administered to patient.

All_symptoms: Inappropriate schedule of product administration No adverse event
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received vaccination earlier than recommended date. Patient 1st dose administered 11/07/2021. Parent scheduled child for 11/20/2021 and received second dose. Patient was supposed to receive second dose on 11/28/2021. Father accompanied child. was advised for 15 minute observation. Child feels fine, no signs or symptoms of adverse reaction. All questions and concerns addressed. Fathers telephone number. Parent and child left facility after 30 minute observation (extra 15 minutes as precaution). Thanks.

5 year old male patient was having trouble being willing to receive vaccine. It took multiple attempts as child was moving around and refusing to be stuck during the time of admin. There was some light bleeding and bruising related to attempts.

All_symptoms: Fatigue Gait disturbance Myositis Pain Pain in extremity
SYMPTOM_TEXT: 6 hours after vaccine: fever to 100.6, fatigue, body aches . Persisted through next day and evening. Resolved by 36h. Around 50 hours, son complaining of leg pain bilaterally causing difficult walking with suspected myositis (similar episode 2 years ago). Resolved in about 12 hours.

Patient received vaccine. Left counseling to sit in observation room. Patient then fainted for about 20 seconds. After, he felt nauseous and had a headache. Continued to observe patient for 30 minutes after fainting and he did begin to feel better. Patient did start to feel better and Dad decided to take him on home. Patient did state that he had not eaten much today.

All_symptoms: Abnormal dreams Cold sweat Crying Hyperhidrosis Immediate post-injection reaction
SYMPTOM_TEXT: The child received vaccine, three seconds later, Site Manager observed the child begin to shake and raise arms in upright and locked position bent at the elbows towards face. At that time RN  was called over and began evaluating child.  RN also came over and began calming child and evaluating him. The child came to within a couple minutes and began crying and stating he did not know what just happened and stated that he had a weird dream. RN began a set of vitals on child where blood pressure was noted to be 101/88 and pulse 58, respirations 22. Child began to sweat profusely and his skin color became pallor. Child's skin was also cold and clammy to touch however child was talking and coherent, child answering questions asked of him appropriately.  EMS was called to scene and arrived at that point began asking child questions which he was answering appropriately.  His skin color and sweating improved before being transported out of facility. Child was taken to Hospital.
Was supposed to get pediatric dose, was given adult dose.

All_symptoms: Incorrect dose administered No adverse event
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received an adult dose of Pfizer instead of the pediatric dose.   Managers, Pediatric Doc, Peds Covid physician (Dr. Notified) Had patient stay a full hour to be monitored.  Mom is a nurse and she called her peds doc. Had pharmacist also speak with mom.  Reassured mom and told her that we would keep her even longer than normal.  The patient was playful and not exhibiting any adverse reactions.

All_symptoms: Fatigue Injection site pain Lymphadenopathy Pain in extremity
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA; fatigue the next day, pain at the injection site and down the arm. No redness at the injection point, swollen lymph nodes on the injection arm side - in the armpit for 4 days after.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Symptoms include pain at the injection site first day, lethargy, headache, fatigue second day and vomiting, rapid heart beat on morning of third day.   48 hours after injection, symptoms subsided.  These seemed more severe for first dose.

All_symptoms: Dizziness Electric shock sensation Headache Hypotension Pallor
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Blurry vision, dizzy, pallor, head ache, ""Felt like I got tazed"" (like electric shock).  Hypotension that took about 30 minutes to resolve.

Pt was accidentally administered a pediatric Covid vaccine instead of the Flu vaccine that they wanted.  I have spoken to their MD and she said she had already spoken to them and told then not to worry, that they would be just fine. They were not experiencing any signs/symptoms and she told them they probably wouldn't and that all would be fine.

All_symptoms: Blood glucose normal Blood pressure decreased Dyskinesia Enuresis Gaze palsy
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Child experienced syncope for 5 seconds and/or seizure. Eyes rolled back, had some jerking movements, became sweaty and wet his pants. Blood pressure dropped to 70s/30s. Blood sugar was 79. Transported to hospital via ambulance.

All_symptoms: Bronchiolitis Chest X-ray abnormal Cough Decreased appetite Fatigue
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Persistent cough was reported to pediatrician on 11/01/2021. Pediatrician saw no issue with the cough. Flu shot was administered this day.  Day of 11/18/2021 patient complained of sore throat. Persistent cough is assumed to be the reason. Patient also had a runny nose. Night of 11/18/2021 patient developed a slight fever (100.6) and had a poor night's rest.  Day of 11/19/2021 child complains of a sore throat and begins to wheeze while simultaneously breathing faster. Patient has a loss of appetite and is fatigued. An at-home COVID-19 rapid test (BinaxNOW) come back with a negative result but due to the problem being a respiratory issue, the patient is taken to the ER at Medical Center in the area.  Nasal swab shows the patient has a rhinovirus and chest x-rays show signs of bronchiolitis.  Oxygen is given to the patient. 3 doses of a respiratory treatment and 1 steroid treatment. Patient is discharged with a prescription for ALBUTEROL 90 mcg/puff inhaler + spacer (monaghan, medium-sized mask spacer) and DEXAMETHASONE (DECADRON) 1mg/mL solution.  Day of 11/20/2021, patient is breathing much easier but still has some wheezing. Coughing has brought up clear phlegm. Pediatrician is called for consultation and no additional notes given. Throat is still sore.
LAB_DATA: Nasal swab: Rhinovirus Chest X-Ray: Bronchiolitis

SYMPTOM_TEXT: HIVES ON FOREHEAD AND BACK OF EAR. ITCHING.

The pfizer vaccine was not diluted prior to administration. 0.2ml of the undiluted vaccine was administered in the left deltoid at 9:12am. This was caught by a coworker in less than an hour and reported to the lead provider. The patient, pfizer manufacturing and poison control were all contacted promptly.

I gave patient his pediatric dose around 5pm and when he was sitting in the waiting area, around 5:20pm, my technician ran over to me and told me she had an emergency and the patient is passing out. I went and assessed the situation to see if he was having a reaction or fainting and noticed he was having syncope. I raised his legs and ran to grab cold backs for his wrists, neck, and face, we gave him something to drink while I directed another technician to call 911. We stayed with the patient, he was reactive and doing okay until paramedics arrived and then we let them take over the rest.

About 5 minutes post vaccine patient began complaining of feeling shaky and a little light headed.  Breathing, color, and mentation appeared fine.  Patient given water and crackers (had not had breakfast) and told to lie down with feet up if he became more lightheaded.  Patient was observed for 20 minutes, during which time he developed chills and became sleepy.    He also had what appeared to be impetigo on nose near left nostril, which the father was advised to seek medical care since it would likely require an oral antibiotic.    Patient appeared stable and was allowed to leave and again father was advised to seek additional care if symptoms worsened and also for evaluation for likely impetigo.     Spoke to father at 12:16 pm, they had gone home since patient was tired and wanted to lie down.   AT home he developed additional chills, body aches and was given tylenol.   The father was calling urgent care to get an appt for son to be evaluated.
Child had 2 fainting episodes and 2 vomiting episodes about 15 minutes apart, EMS arrived at around 12:45p.m , took vitals and transported child to the hospital.
fainted

After a child received the Pfizer pediatric vaccine, they became pale, light headed, and weak. The pharmacist had them lie on the floor and applied a cold compress. Another child who also received the same vaccine saw what occurred to their sibling and became nauseous and vomited. After 30 minutes of the pharmacist observing them, both children felt better and left with their family.

My 7y/o son had a hard large moveable lump alongside his jawline. It was 1cm x .5 cm. I took him to the pediatricians office the day after we noticed it. The doctor said it felt like a large lymph node, which was a reaction to the COVID-19 vaccine and it should go down with time. I had never felt a lymph node like that - that size and firmness.
Pt. stated he felt dizzy. Pt placed in recumbent position, observed, vitals taken.  Pt. returned home to with mom.

i administered pfizer 5-11 vaccine to patient - he was very brave and sat still , did nit cry. he was getting it because he has 2  younger brothers . At that point he was fine. a few minutes later his mother was holding him saying that his legs felt limp. i layed him back on a chair , applied a cold water bottle to his wrist and forehead , asked if his tongue felt funny - it did not - and kept taking to him while also having front store manager call 911 . a few minutes later patient said h that he was ok and I asked if he wanted some water -which he did. I explained to him that the firefighters would be coming to check his breathing . they observed him and put him on a stretcher. I called his mother at 6:45 pm to check on him. she stated that they thought that he had a panic attack, and the he would see his pedi md on Monday. Mother also stated that patient was back to normal and was eating and playing all afternoon.
Allergic reaction- itching and red rash on scalp, neck, ears and shoulder

About three days after the first dose, the skin around and underneath my daughter's nose started to develop discolored patches that looked like vitiligo. My wife and I thought it might could be a rash or the normal skin changes that happen in young children. This was Tuesday, Nov. 16. On Nov. 18, a dermatologist confirmed that my daughter had vitiligo patches around her nose. In the course of two days, the spots had quickly become lighter in color, as if the discoloration was accelerating. She was prescribed Elidel cream for six weeks.

All_symptoms: Feeling abnormal Loss of consciousness Mydriasis Posture abnormal Respiratory rate increased
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client was given the flu shot first and then their Pfizer shot. About 10 seconds after the Pfizer shot he started to feel ""weird"" and breathing faster. His eyes got bigger (dilated) and he put his head back. We're pretty sure he passed out at that point. The pharmacist that administered the shot called for assistance. By the time the assistance came within 15 seconds he was coming around more alert. The emergency kit was grabbed. At that point the administering Pharmacist started to go through a breathing method to calm the client. He started to calm and breath in a normal pattern. The client was alert at this point and responding to questions correctly. The client and father waited close by for observation for 30 minutes. The client was alert, breathing well and feeling much better when they left.

About 38 hours after shot, red patches/welches appeared in chest and upper back and have slowly gotten worse. As of today, 11/20, red welts are spreading to hairline and trunk and down back. Now he is saying they feel like they are ?burning?.
LAB_DATA: We have talked to our pediatricians office and they said since no fever or trouble breathing or itching not much they can do. I talked to them twice with same advice. My son?s  Itching started today (11/20).  We asked a pharmacist for advice today and he said Zyrtec and hydrocortisone cream but if this doesn?t help or stop rash we should seek medical attention.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Swollen lump under the eye.

At approximately 3:11 PM on 11/20/2021, male child arrives to vaccine site with his father. Child's father requests initial pediatric Pfizer dose to be administered to child.  Nurse attempted to begin administering dose and poked with needle in left upper arm. Needle was inserted approximately 3 cm, then child withdrew arm and moved away from nurse. Child was difficult to console, and none of vaccine dose was administered to the child. Pfizer pediatric dose was not given to child for safety reasons. This dose and syringe was wasted, per COSD Policy guidelines.

All_symptoms: Fatigue Headache Incorrect dose administered Pain in extremity
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Mom took son with her to a Pfizer clinic.  PT went through screening process and was administered an adult Pfizer as this was a booster clinic.  Mom made aware of med error while waiting to be discharged from the clinic.  Clinic educated parents to follow up with PCP, PCP encouraged parents to follow up with DOH.  Dad called into DOH to inquire what to do next with dosing.  Dad reports that patients experienced typical side effects of fatigue, HA, and sore arm.  Dad asking questions of what to look and what to be concerned about because child was administered the wrong formulation.  DOH physician followed up with education with family.  11/22/2021: Spoke with clinic, Recommended that they complete a VAERS form and educated on how to do that, verbalized understanding.   She reported that patient's mom signed him up for the clinic and he was administered the dose by a new nurse who asked his age after administration.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 6 year old ex 28 week twin male with hx of grade 3 IVH and VP shunt  (last revised 8/2020) with recently diagnosed focal epilepsy, well controlled on Keppra.  He received his first dose of Pfizer vaccine on 11/6 around 9:30 am. The next day, dad states he c/o headache and some stomach upset.  On 11/7 in the evening, he had 1x episode of emesis just prior to bed.  After this episode, per dad, he was staring into space and not responsive.  Denies eye deviation or extremity shaking.  EMS was called and was intermittently sleepy and not back to baseline for ~1 hour.     Patient was seen initially at where he had a reassuring BMP, CBC.  They gave him his evening dose of Keppra via IV.  He was then transferred to for further management given VP shunt and concern for seizure.   No fevers, headache, diarrhea, rash, URI symptoms within the week leading up to the vaccine.   Last (and first) seizure was in January 2021.  Takes daily Keppra.  Last medication change was around March 2021.
LAB_DATA: CT Scan and shunt series at on 11/8 were at baseline. He was negative for flu and Sars-CoV-2 on RPP.CBC and BMP were normal.
HISTORY: Patient is a 6 year  old boy, ex 28 week twin, with PMHx significant for grade III IVH, hydrocephalus s/p VP shunt, reactive airway disease, global developmental delays, ADHD and localization related epilepsy on daily Keppra. Seizures have been well controlled. First and only seizure was in January 2021.

All_symptoms: Asthenia Cough Dysphonia Dyspnoea Pharyngeal swelling
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received his vaccine on Tuesday, by Wednesday early evening he presented with low energy, but otherwise good spirits.  By 7pm when his temp was taken he had a 104.7 degree temp.  Cognitives were good, mood was good.  Dose of Children's 10ml (320mg) Tylenol at 7pm and again at 12am (Thursday Morning).  Thursday 7:30am Morning temp rested at 103.5.  Another dose of Children's 10ml Tylenol (320mg) at 7:30am and fever began to wane over the course of the day.  Again Children's 10ml Tylenol  (320mg) at Thursday 4pm temp was 102.6.    At 9pm on Thursday patient's voice started to become raspy, but was still in good mood.  Again, Children's 10ml Tylenol (320mg) at 12am (Friday).  Friday Morning 7:30am  temp was resting at 99.0, however patient was having a hard time breathing and his voice was significantly worse.  Patient presented with a dry cough and difficulty catching breath.  The cough was like Croup, deep in chest, and reverberated through esophagus.    He was given another does of Children's 10ml Tylenol  (320mg) Friday at 7:30am, and a 5ml of Infant Ibuprofen (200mg) for throat swelling, and one dose of Albuterol Inhaler (90 mcg) to alleviate difficulty breathing.  We then practiced breathing exercises to calm him down, which worked fairly well.  His coughing subsided, and we administered 5ml Children's Cough DM (30mg dextramethorphan hydrobromide) to suppress coughing.  By 2:15pm (now) his voice has started to come back, but is still raspy and he feels better.
LAB_DATA: None, just the injection of the Covid Vaccine

All_symptoms: Abdominal pain upper Appendicitis Asthenia Blindness Blood test
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received the vaccine on Monday, November 8th. She was not anxious to get the vaccine, she was excited and proud to get it. She didn't have lunch before the vaccine, but did have cereal for breakfast. Immediately after getting the vaccine (while still sitting in the chair), Patient held her head and said ""my head mommy, my head hurts so much"" and then they had her stand up and she opened her eyes wide and said ""I can't see mommy, everything is white"" and I asked the person who gave the vaccine to help. She laid patient on the ground and put her feet up. She was clammy, very pale, and still. She shivered a little as if she was cold. She laid there with tears, but awake for about 20 minutes. They brought a wheelchair and moved her to a cot. We gave her some crackers and they asked us to leave about 10 minutes later.   She was very tired following the event and for the rest of the day, but she was awake and talking and walking. On Tuesday and Wednesday, she complained of a ""bad headache"" and said her ears and her head were hot.  On Thursday she was a little pale, but didn't complain of anything. On Friday in school they sent her to the school nurse becasue she was pale and clammy and said her head hurt really bad.   On Saturday (11/13) evening, she started throwing up. She threw up and had water-diarrhea all day on Sunday. She coudn't sit up or move on her own.   I took her to a Pediatric Urgent Care on Monday (11/15), and they sent us to the Hospital Emergency Room (details below). They tested her for everything they could think of, and the only abnormal result was a positive Strep test.   Today is Thursday (11/18) and she has been at home since we left the ER on Monday, but only very slowly feeling better. She hasn't eaten much since Saturday (11/13), though she is drinking fine. She has thrown up 1-2 times each day and still feels very weak and tired. She's slept most of the day, every day. This morning is the first time she's willingly eaten a little bit. She's definitely not been herself over the past 5 days.   I'm honestly terrified to get her the second dose of the vaccine. I realize the illness could be completely unrelated to the vaccine, but I'd like to get an opinion on whether or not to get her the second dose on time, or wait a while.
LAB_DATA: The pediatric Urgent Care tested her for COVID, flu, and urinary tract infection. All were negative. They suspected that she may have appendicitis because of the severity of her vomiting, diarrhea, and stomach pain when we were in the office and sent us to the Emergency Room.   I took her directly to the ER, where they did blood tests, a strep test, an ultrasound, and gave her IV fluids. The only abnormal finding was a positive strep test and a lot of gas in her stomach. They sent her home with Amoxicillin and she has taken it 2x a day since.
HISTORY: No chronic or long-standing health conditions or concerns

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt recieved vaccine and immediately jumped up from her seat to run around with her friends, 5 minutes post vaccine she felt dizzy, warm, decreased hearing and felt like she would pass out.  Attempted to lower her to the floor, but father refused holding her in his lap.  She is pale, responsive, VS 84/58, HR 105, RR 16, O2 95% RA, no respiratory distress, difficulty breathing, water given, nothing to eat/drink in 5 hours.  1 minute later child stated, ""I feel much better, I can hear now and I'm not dizzy anymore.""  Client talkative, describing her experience, color has returned to her cheeks, tolerating additional water and graham crackers.  Observed until 17:35 when she ambulated without incident with her father out of the clinic.

No SOB, no chest tightness, no wheezing, no acute distress.  MD notified, assessed patient, and ordered Benadryl 25mg PO x1.  Rash did not spread, no itchiness.  Pt observed for another 20 minutes.  Rash did not spread.  Parent felt comfortable taking the patient home with a follow up with PCP.

All_symptoms: Anxiety Condition aggravated Fear Headache Pain
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Given a 5-11 pfizer vaccine at 1:40 pm.    At 1:50 HPM was called over to first aid station where pt had been taken. She c/o jaw pain and feelings of fear stating ""Is something bad going to happen to me?"".  HPM instructed pt to lay down on cot. 1:55 pm: HR = 110; RR = 22 BP 106/80; O2 sat 99% Alert and oriented, Respiration unlabored, Skin warm and dry, facial paleness, no rash noted, capillary refill <2 secs.  HPM reassured child that she was being taken care of and other clinic RN encouraged regular steady breathing. Jaw pain subsided and pt started to c/o upper left thigh pain which subsided when she bent her leg with knee to ceiling.  Mother reports that pt has anxiety around unknown situations such as the vaccine clinic and has experienced similar symptoms of increased fear in the past. Observed for 30 minutes during which pt continued to voice concern stating ""I'm really scared, am I going to be o.k. Voice clear and strong, c/o headache stating ""this always happen to me when I get scared"".  Mom speaking calmly and quietly to child which was effective in bringing anxiety down. Mom verified verbally that pt gets a headache when she is upset.  2:20 HR = 92  BP 102/72.  Skin warm and dry, facial paleness resolved, no rash noted. No further complaints of pain. Walked family to car and gave instructions about when to be concerned, when to call MD (anxiety continues), when to go to ER (rash, concerned), when to call 911(swelling of tongue, throat, trouble talking, drooling, trouble breathing, loses consciousness). Mom verbalized understanding.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had a fever for approximately 3 days at times over 103 that was difficult to keep in control by keeping cool cloths on him under a fan and alternating tylenol and motrin. He said his body hurt and that he didn't feel well. He experienced significant congestion and he told his dad that it was hard to breath. I am not sure if it was hard to breath bc of congestion or if he was having any respiratory issues. He was significantly congested for several days. Patient stayed home from school due to his symptoms for 3 days. Patient saw a doctor who thought he probably picked up a cold at the exact same time he received his first covid vaccine dose, as Patient's 3 year old brother started experiencing the same symptoms approximately 5 days after Patient received his covid vaccine. It is just strange that a cold would happen at the exact same time that a covid vaccine was received. It is possible that it was a cold, but it is also possible that Patient had pretty significant symptoms in response to the covid vaccine. I thpught it should be reported in case other people experience the same thing.
LAB_DATA: Dose received 11/10/21, called pediatrician on 11/11/21. Went to urgent care on 11/14/21.  Patient's symptoms were cough, rhinorrhea, and congestion. Home covid test was negative on 11/14/21

All_symptoms: Bradycardia Feeling cold Head injury Heart rate decreased Hyperhidrosis
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Per Mothers report: Patient was vaccinated, then watched his brother get vaccinated and said ""whoa"", then walked to the waiting area and was looking at items when he got pale and slumped against his brother down to the floor.   He apparently lost consciousness momentarily or certainly lost clarity.   Mother called for help and patient was placed on a cot.  Mother called for help.   I found the patient to be diaphoretic, cool, and bradycardic with a weak pulse by palpation at the wrist.  There was no rash, redness, nor airway tightness.  Indications were that this was a case of syncope.   There was no witness of a head injury and no scalp tenderness.  Legs were elevated and patient drank sips of water.  After 20 minutes, with parents collaboration, patient was moved outdoors to ""fresh air"" where he sat on a chair several minutes and then walked slowly then rapidly, finally achieving better color and a strong pulse.   Patient went home with both parents - on e driving and one observing.   Call back at 4:50 pm (approx 2.5 hrs after vaccination) the patient was snacking and drinking and improving slowly.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient started developing a cough on Saturday, November 13 around 7:45 PM.  She started fevering, having body aches, and an upset stomach Sunday, November 14 around 2:30 PM.  On Monday, November 15, she early in the morning, she started throwing up.  She decided to stay home from school.  Late that morning, we called into her doctors office to see if she should be seen and if they had an appointment.  They wanted her to be seen but didn't have any available times to be seen that day and instructed us to go to an urgent care clinic.  Upon doing so, they checked her out, said all her vitals were good, ran a rapid strep test, and a 3-in-1 Flu, Covid, and RSV test.  The strep test, Covid test, and Flu test all came back as negative.  The RSV test came back positive.  As such, there was no adverse reaction to the vaccine, and instead, she had come down with RSV.
LAB_DATA: Rapid strep test, 3-in-1 Covid/Flu/RSV (SARS-CoV-2, Influenza, RSV by PCR, POC) test.

Medical lead followed up with mother, via text, on 11/15 who confirmed that patient, ""was good most of the day yesterday [Sunday 11/14], but got hit last evening. He slept well and awoke today much better.""  Medical lead enocouraged mother to reach out by phone, text, or email should any other symptoms develop in the patient. All side effects sound to be within expected side effect profile after COVID19 mRNA vaccine receipt.  After-midday break, vaccine tables and vaccinators were separated by vaccine type. No additional mix-ups reported, supported by all matching number of vaccine expected for each age group and number up vaccines drawn from vials.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 48 pound, 9 year old girl received her first Pfizer covid vaccine.  Gave vaccine and she was fine, but her arm was bleeding a lot.  About 2 minutes later she started to get up and went completely white and got dizzy.  We sat her down and got an ice pack right away.  She was not regaining her color and felt nauseated, but could not throw up.  She never completely lost consciousness but was going in and out.  We called emergency number. She started to get very hot and sweaty.  Her blood pressure with an adult cuff was 116/87 and pulse was 37.  She never regained color and the squad got there.  They checked her blood pressure (a little low), pulse (normal), blood sugar (normal), ekg normal.  After about 30 minutes she started to get some color back in her lips.  She tried to stand up again and was starting to feel a little better.  The squad had her wait another couple minutes and had her get up and walk and turn in a circle to make sure she would be okay on her feet.  She sat back down and started to regain more color in her face.  The squad left about 40 minutes after the vaccination was given.  She did not leave the store in the ambulance.  She went home with dad since she was feeling better.  More than likely vasovagal response, she never did pass out completely.

On November 14, 2021 at 3:45pm my daughter stated that she felt a strong amount of pressure in her head.  She described the pressure  and pain similar to a headache.  She stated a short time later that she felt like everything was spinning around her.  When given a dose of Tylenol she stated that it slowed it down but she still felt like she was spinning.  She went to bed on Sunday evening and woke up Monday morning November 15, 2021 stating that her symptoms were the same feeling a spinning motion and pressure in her head.  She again was given Tylenol which she stated again made the feeling slightly go away but still present.  When I contacted her Primary Care Physician she stated that it would be best to go to the local Emergency Room for a further evaluation.  At the Emergency room she was evaluated and a Neurological Physical Assessment was done by the ER doctors.  At this time she had no remarkable signs of any significant neurological deficits.  She was discharged and we were told to follow up if symptoms persisted.  As of 9:16am on November 16, 2021 she is still stating that she has the same head pressure and spinning feeling.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: He woke in the middle of the night crying out and experiencing severe pain in his left hip/side/back. He reported it was the worst pain he ever experienced, and was insistent it was not gas pain. His forehead felt warm, but not his cheeks, and I did not take his temperature. I asked him to try to go back to sleep, and we would see how he felt in the morning. He was unable to go back to sleep, but his forehead felt markedly cooler in the morning several hours later (which made me wish I had taken his temperature). The pain subsided and he was able to go to school.  The day of his vaccine, he reported some leg muscle weakness and ""shaky feeling"" in his legs, and was limping slightly about 4 hours post-vaccination. I had a fairly strong reaction of joint pain after my 2nd Moderna dose, so I wondered if it might be a similar reaction?  We went to the doctor for a previously-scheduled well check on Thursday (the day after the hip pain). She stated it could be several things, probably not connected to the vaccine. I agree with this, but wanted to pass along since it a new vaccine to this age group.

At the end of the COVID vaccine clinic on 11/11/2021 at approximately 1715 I, RN Nurse Manager of the clinic realized that additional doses of the COVID clinic would need to be mixed and drawn up for the remaining patients on the schedule. I went into the medication room to mix a vial of the COVID vaccine with normal saline as I had been taught to do earlier in the day with Pharmacist. I opened the red bag of supplies to mix up the vaccine and only found one vial in the bag with a salmon colored top. Remembering that that the vaccine came in a vial with an orange top I believed this to be the vaccine and was looking for the diluent. Unable to locate some I called pharmacist and she informed me that I was fine to use normal saline from another source to mix the vaccine. I located another source of normal saline within the clinic and used it to mix 1.3ml of normal saline into the vial. After following the mixing instructions of inverting the initial vial 10x, added the diluent, removed 1.3ml of air, and then inverted the vial 10x to mix, I then drew up multiple syringes of 0.2ml RN and MA each took two syringes to vaccinators who were waiting to administer the vaccine to patients. approximately 10-15 minutes later another HCP and I called pharmacist to ensure I knew how to properly dispose of the unused vaccine. It was during this conversation that I realized I had not used the COVID vaccine vial but had used the diluent vial and had mixed additional NACL into the diluent vial. I immediately asked who had received the last 4 doses, 3 of those patients were still in the building and 1 patient had left. I notified the parents of the 3 patients who were still on the premises of the error that was made and apologized. I then asked if they would still like the patient to receive the COVID vaccine tonight and the parents agreed. Those 3 patients each received a dose after I went back into the med room and correctly mixed the vaccine. The patients remained under observation for 15 minutes and were then discharged. None of these patients experienced any negative effects while under observation. A phone call and message was left/sent to the parent of the 4th patient that night and the following morning another phone call was placed to the patient's father and the situation explained. Father agreed to bring the patient in on the following Monday in order to receive the COVID vaccine.

After following the mixing instructions of inverting the initial vial 10x, added the diluent, removed 1.3ml of air, and then inverted the vial 10x to mix, I then drew up multiple syringes of 0.2ml RN adjunct professor  and  MA each took two syringes to vaccinators who were waiting to administer the vaccine to patients. approximately 10-15 minutes later staff member and I called pharmacist to ensure I knew how to properly dispose of the unused vaccine. It was during this conversation that I realized I had not used the COVID vaccine vial but had used the diluent vial and had mixed additional NACL into the diluent vial. I immediately asked who had received the last 4 doses, 3 of those patients were still in the building and 1 patient had left. I notified the parents of the 3 children who were still on the premises of the error that was made and apologized. I then asked if they would still like their child(ren) to receive the COVID vaccine tonight and the parents agreed. Those 3 children each received a dose after I went back into the med room and correctly mixed the vaccine. The children remained under observation for 15 minutes and were then discharged. None of these children experienced any negative effects while under observation.

All_symptoms: Dizziness Lethargy Loss of consciousness Pallor Syncope
SYMPTOM_TEXT: 7 year old female patient received dose 1 of the pediatric formulation (orange cap) of Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine. Approximately 5 minutes after patient was immunized, she reported feeling light headed. The nurse immunizer helped the patient sit down in her dad's lap. She became pale and lethargic though was speaking and breathing regularly. The healthcare provider on-site (PA-C) was alerted of the situation, and immediately responded to the patient. The patient then had a brief loss of consciousness for about 3 seconds. She was immediately laid down during that time and awoke when aroused. Pulse was 90bpm with a regular rhythm and SpO2 94 on RA. With deep and controlled breathing, SpO2 rose to 98 on RA within 1 minute. EMS was called as a precaution. The patient denied trouble breathing or swallowing, and there were no signs of external rashes or inflammation. Parents denied transport to medical facility or emergency room. Paramedic and PA-C agreed that this was a vasovagal syncopal event.

All_symptoms: Blood culture negative Crying Culture negative Dyskinesia Headache
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Developed a low-grade fever early in the day on 11/9/2021; displayed flu-like symptoms throughout the day. At around 6:30pm our son began to cry an inconsolable cry and complained of severe pain in his neck on the right side of his body, along with severe head pain. The pain limited his range of motion with his head/neck for the next 36 or so hours. It was difficult for him to control movement at onset. We monitored him at home through the night of 11/9/2021. We made an appointment on 11/10/2021 with our son?s pediatrician and she first did a rapid strep test, which was negative. After those results we did a COVID swab, as well as a viral panel for lab work, and submitted the other strep swab for culture. She ruled out meningitis on 11/10/21 due to the fever being controlled with ibuprofen, as well as him being successful with bending his head forward and backward.  At 2am on 11/12/21 we received negative results for his strep culture. At 7:30am on 11/12/21 we received all negative results for his viral panel. His pediatrician also ordered a blood culture if all results from the COVID and viral panel were negative. At 9:30am on 11/12/21 we completed the blood culture. By 1:30pm we received the culture results and our pediatrician called around 5pm to confirm that the results of his lab work all fell within normal pediatric ranges. No further followup was needed. The fever stopped on 11/11/21. The pain in the neck and head lessened each day and was completely gone by 11/14/21.
LAB_DATA: We made an appointment on 11/10/2021 with our son?s pediatrician and she first did a rapid strep test, which was negative. After those results we did a COVID swab, as well as a viral panel for lab work, and submitted the other strep swab for culture. At 2am on 11/12/21 we received negative results for his strep culture. At 7:30am on 11/12/21 we received all negative results for his viral panel.   His pediatrician also ordered a blood culture if all results from the COVID and viral panel were negative. At 9:30am on 11/12/21 we completed the blood culture. By 1:30pm we received the culture results and our pediatrician called around 5pm to confirm that the results of his lab work all fell within normal pediatric ranges.

All_symptoms: Injection site erythema Injection site pruritus Injection site rash
SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt got her vaccination on Sunday evening, 11/7.  On Thursday evening, 11/11 she complained of an itchy arm as she was getting ready for bed.  We looked, and her left arm, and it was lumpy and red 1-2 inches away from her injection site. The lumps didn't exactly look like hives (which she sometimes gets), and it was not symmetrical around the injection site. I called a friend who is doctor and a infectious disease specialist, who asked if pt was having trouble breathing.  She was not.  My friend said she could have some Benadryl or Claritin or whatever we usually would offer her if she was itchy or having hives.  So we gave her 5 mL of Benadryl. Pt has complained of some itchiness since (and we have given Benadryl another evening one time), the redness has decreased but some of the lumps are still there, if reduced.
HISTORY: Eczema; earwax leading to hearing difficulties (we think).

All_symptoms: Arthralgia Cough Gait disturbance Henoch-Schonlein purpura Joint stiffness
SYMPTOM_TEXT: The two nights following the vaccine resulted in low fever while sleeping and some whimpering. He attended school the next day (Wednesday) but stayed home Thursday and Friday due to a congested cough that 3 family members had. patient started limping on Thursday afternoon following a very restful day. He complained of L ankle pain.  Friday was fairly normal without complaints until the evening before bed. Then he woke with significant pain during the night. He slept until 10:00am the next morning and had a typical day helping with yard work and relaxing. He again complained of pain in the afternoon and upon examination had a circular, oblong ring shaped rash on posterior L ankle. He woke again that night in pain. Sunday was better in the morning but symptoms worsened earlier in the day, with another circular bruise like rash seen on medial aspect of R foot. He was in significant pain. Also noted swelling in knees and complaints of pain L>R .Stiffness, limping, point tenderness and sensitivity all present at rash sites. Symptoms worsen as the day goes on. Sunday night he slept through the night after having ibuprofen.  He attended school Monday and then saw doctor at 1:30. Rash had worsened. Again worse at 8pm. Applied aquaphor and gave ibuprofen. Limping and stiffness when going to bed with moderate pain.
LAB_DATA: Saw dr.  11/15/21. Urinary analysis 11/15/21 showed protein in urine.  Suspected HSP Kidney function and strep test ordered for 11/16/21
